{
  "texts": [
    "Low concentrations of NO (<100 nmol/L) may promote tumor development by inhibiting apoptosis and stimulating endothelial cell proliferation.",
    "In contrast, high concentrations of NO (400-1000 nmol/L) would disrupt the cell cycle and accelerate cellular apoptosis (82).",
    "Because tumor cells rely on arginine in the TME, depriving tumors of arginine has emerged as a novel anti-tumor therapy and has shown encouraging efficacy in clinical trials against certain types of cancer.",
    "However, simply depriving arginine not only starves tumor cells but also impairs the anti-tumor immune response.",
    "Geiger et al."
  ]
}